Describes the plague pandemic known as the Black Death, including how it spread throughout Europe, contemporary medical treatments, and the social and religious impacts of the plague.

Most Helpful Customer Review
Informative
By Ann Tufariello on June 25, 2009
Format: Library Binding
This is a well-researched book with detailed illustrations that bring the Black Death to life for the reader. While the target market is middle school students, anyone interested in learning about the Black Death would benefit from this book. In concise language, the book explains what the black death was, how it spread, and what the consequences were.
